## 3. Submission Requirements
- **Email Submission**: PDF only, max 5 MB per email, all pages numbered.
- **Volumes**: Technical & Past Performance, Price.
- **SAM Registration and UEI required.**
- **Safety Program**: Written procedures included.
- **Amendments**: Must acknowledge all solicitation amendments.
- **Contact**: James Postell (james.postell@va.gov)

## 4. Compliance & Insurance
- **Insurance Minimums**: As defined by FAR 28.307-2 and 52.228-5; generally covers workers’ compensation, general and automotive liability. (Check solicitation for exact coverage levels.)
- **Safety & Inspection**: VA will inspect and require written safety program adherence.
- **Government Provided**: Utilities, trash, trays, hard plates, utensils, fire suppression system maintenance.
- **Relevant Clauses**: FAR/VAAR requirements on options, rejected goods, electronic payment.

## 5. Special Requirements/Operational Issues
- **No incumbent**—new requirement due to renovation.
- **No photos/floor plans**; site visit may be arranged.
- **High sensitivity/at-risk populations require special dietary accommodations.**
- **No union mandate or clinical/medical care required.**

## 6. Opportunity Fit vs. Disqualification Checklist
**Potential Flags/Disqualifiers:**
- Location: Hawaii (not CA/NY/IL, so QUALIFIED)
- Scope: EVS/dietary/food service FITS primary model. No medical care required.
- Timeline: >2 week proposal window (QUALIFIED). Startup period not specified, but acceptable.
- Insurance: Standard (not excessive), QUALIFIED.
- Contract value: Typically above $250k/year. (Check full budget if available.)

**Summary Judgment:**
This solicitation aligns well with the qualifications checklist: fits dietary scope, location and operational conditions appear acceptable (Hawaii), insurance and compliance seem standard for the industry, and proposal timeline is generous.

**Recommendation:** **Qualified for Pursuit.**
- Proceed to detailed review of solicitation language and pricing terms, confirm contract ceiling and scoring system, and verify no union or specialized capital asset requirement.

